thread.title: The Falcon Heavy: A Good Show, but Not Necessarily Great Business

author: Andy Pasztor
title: The Falcon Heavy: A Good Show, but Not Necessarily Great Business
text:
WASHINGTON—The launch this week of SpaceX’s mammoth Falcon Heavy rocket was a feat, but many in the space industry doubt it will bring the company big commercial business.
The heavy-lift vehicle appears to be too small for ferrying crews or delivering major cargo packages into deep space, said executives attending a commercial space conference here Wednesday. At the same time, it seems too big to serve today’s generation of smaller satellites, they added.
